entries.title: Elon Musk's 'lies' about Tesla on Twitter cost investors millions, court told
entries.description: Elon Musk "lied" when he claimed he had "secured" funding to take Tesla private, a lawyer for investors has told a court.

entries.title: Major blow for Zelenskyy as he loses key minister in battle against Russia
entries.description: "Go to hell" was the message that Ukraine's war-time interior minister had at the mention of Russian President Vladimir Putin.

entries.title: Nobel Peace Prize winner cleared of 'bogus' tax evasion charges
entries.description: Nobel Peace Prize winner Maria Ressa has been cleared of tax evasion charges that human rights charities said were "bogus and politically motivated".

entries.title: Turning point in European Parliament scandal as insider lifts the lid on corruption
entries.description: It has already been a dramatic investigation, but the corruption scandal at the European Parliament has now taken an extraordinary lurch.

entries.title: Ireland launches €2.5bn scheme to repair fire safety defects in homes
entries.description: The Irish government has approved a repair scheme costing up to €2.5bn (£2.2bn) to fix fire safety and other defects in 100,000 apartments and duplexes built during Ireland's Celtic Tiger boom era.

entries.title: Sniffer dogs, beware: Scientists give robot a sense of smell
entries.description: A robot has been given a sense of smell thanks to groundbreaking research which will put the fear of redundancy into sniffer dogs everywhere.

entries.title: Female footballer wins landmark £72,000 maternity payout in 'wake-up call' for clubs
entries.description: A female footballer has been awarded more than £72,000 in back-dated maternity leave pay in a landmark victory she hailed as a "wake-up call" for football clubs.

entries.title: French city asks Madonna if it can borrow a painting it lost in 1918
entries.description: The French city of Amiens has appealed to Madonna to lend it a painting it lost in 1918 - because she bought it in 1989.

entries.title: Teenage mother and 10-month-old baby among six killed in California shooting
entries.description:
A teenage mother and her 10-month-old baby were fatally shot in the head 
"assassination style" in an attack that left six people dead in central California.

entries.title: Ukrainian minister among 18 dead in helicopter crash near Kyiv
entries.description: The Minister of Internal Affairs of Ukraine is among 18 people who have died after a helicopter crashed  by a nursery in a Kyiv suburb, authorities have said.

entries.title: End ban on bare breasts, Instagram and Facebook told
entries.description: Facebook and Instagram could be about to "free the nipple" after owners Meta's oversight board said nudity rules on the sites should be overhauled.

entries.title: China 'more likely' to invade Taiwan and attack could come in 2027 - island's foreign minister
entries.description: Taiwan's foreign minister has said he believes China is now "more likely" to invade Taiwan to distract from leader Xi Jinping's domestic problems.

entries.title: Polar bear kills woman and boy in a remote village in Alaska
entries.description: A polar bear has attacked and killed a woman and boy in a remote village in western Alaska.

entries.title: State-of-the-art bionic arms given to Ukrainian soldiers who were badly wounded by landmines
entries.description: Two Ukrainian soldiers who had amputations after being wounded by landmines are being fitted with state-of-the-art bionic arms made in the UK.
